AuditLogger
public class Logger
extends org.apache.log4j.Logger

This class provides additional functionality over the Logger class provided in Log4j. Instances of this class are obtained through the static getLogger() method. For the levels INFO, WARN, and ERROR, the messages are internationalized and require a messageID for their first parameter. This parameter will be used to lookup the message in a known resource file. The resource file can be found by looking for the file Log..csv where categoryName is the name of the category that is having the message logged to. Unlike Fmt.Sil where you pass the name of the resource file (StringTable) LogMessageCategory does this step for you based on the categoryName used.
